    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-05-16T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-05-16T05:00:00-05:00" n="97"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d97">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 U.S.S.R./55: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_BWC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-16T13:00:00+03:00"
                            >May 16, 1934—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 16—10:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>84. Your 77, May 15, 1 [<hi rend="italic">6</hi>] p.m. I shall see <persName
                        corresp="#p_KNN1">Krestinsky</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_REV1"
                        >Rubinin</persName> this afternoon and attempt to persuade them to enter
                    into discussions on the basis of the Department’s original draft agreement.
                    Would appreciate reply to question numbered 4 in my 81, May 13, noon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
